    "To look for an oscillation pattern in the energy dependence of the ratio of C 4 ∕C 2, the second phase of the beam energy scan (BES-II) was conducted at RHIC.",
    "The BES-II data analyses are under way.In addition, it is predicted that density fluctuations near the QCD critical point can be probed via an intermittency analysis in relativistic heavy ion collisions [162,163].",
    "Figure 21 shows the energy dependence of the scaling exponent () for identified charged hadrons in Au+ Au collisions for two different collision centralities (0-5% and 10-40%) [161].",
    "In the most central collisions, exhibits a non-monotonic behavior as a function of collision energy, reaching a minimum around √ s NN = 20 -30 GeV.",
    "In con- trast, for 10-40% central collisions, remains approximately constant with increasing √ s NN."
